---
description: Version control and commit message standards
globs:
alwaysApply: agent
---

- Use conventional commit format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`.
- Types: feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore, style, perf.
- Include ticket reference when applicable: `feat(auth): add login flow [{{ISSUE_PREFIX}}-123]`.
- Follow the PR template for pull requests.
- Before committing: ensure documentation is updated per `.github/instructions/documentation.instructions.md` (spec, plan, API docs, README, changelog).
- Include documentation changes in the same commit or PR as the code they describe.
